addr="alex-nelson"
title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>We follow Dummit and Foote in defining the Galois group of an extension so that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex> has the maximal number of automorphisms. Some authors are more generous and just treat the Galois group as a synonym for the Automorphism group for field extensions, <fr:em>any</fr:em> arbitrary field extension.</fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>
 
